{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"ARCHITECTURE DECISION (brainstorm outcome, grounded across 3 deep-research rounds + codebase/web spikes; full trail in session log ad3f-2d99-6d41-40e6 'boom-demon-jug'):\n\nCONVERGED STACK (pressure-tested; evidence SUPPORTS it):\n1. ENGINE = a thin homegrown synchronous declarative INTERPRETER over a tailored lean YAML/JSON IR (steps + conditionals + loops + map/fan-out), with run-state on rebar's event log. Building (not adopting) is EVIDENCE-BACKED: every durable-execution library (DBOS=Postgres/SQLite, Restate=server+own log) OWNS its persistence and none can defer to an external git-backed event log; the off-the-shelf wheels don't fit the event-sourced axle. SpiffWorkflow/BPMN rejected as the engine (owns run-state via whole-workflow serialization; heavy BPMN data model; no native agent step; LGPL).\n2. AGENT RUNTIME = a PROVIDER-AGNOSTIC runtime behind the existing Runner seam, REPLACING LangChain/LangGraph (its sole original justification, native Langfuse tracing, is gone — Langfuse is OTel-native in 2026). HARD REQUIREMENT (user): cross-provider; an Anthropic-only solution is REJECTED -> the raw-anthropic-SDK+output_format option is OUT. Leading: Pydantic AI (pydantic-ai-slim[anthropic,...]) with structured output via PromptedOutput (provider-agnostic AND avoids the Claude thinking + forced-tool-choice 400). Keep LangGraph only as the per-agent-step runtime until the swap is proven. ENFORCE the seam strictly (Pydantic AI has 2.0-beta churn + a maintainer-bandwidth crunch) so the dep stays swappable.\n3. VISUAL EDITING = a thin IR<->standard-format serializer feeding an OFF-THE-SHELF embeddable editor (bpmn-js or draw.io) as an EPHEMERAL projection, NEVER persisted. Validated by n8n/Windmill cautionary tales (DB-vs-file dual-store reconciliation pain) and Kestra's compact declarative agent-step encoding (the template to copy). Visual format choice (bpmn-js vs draw.io) settled by a round-trip POC.\n\nCONTROL FLOW (executor spike): conditionals/loops trip the documented Burr triggers; resolved by a synchronous worklist interpreter (still no async/threading -> tripwire intact, override recorded). Iteration-keyed run-state markers + mandatory max_iterations (each iteration is a committed, auto-pushed event).\n\nDE-RISK POCs (next, grounded in the Inspect AI eval seam + 3 corpuses): (1) RUNTIME — Pydantic AI behind the seam, PromptedOutput, on >=2 PROVIDERS, asserting structured-output validity + zero-400 under extended thinking + Langfuse-OTel trace fidelity; (2) ENGINE — thin interpreter, prove resume/replay correctness over the event log (kill mid-run -> replay from events -> no double-effects); (3) VISUAL — IR<->editor round-trip property test (bpmn-js vs draw.io), semantic + ID + agent-metadata fidelity, visual never persisted. Experiments live under docs/experiments (reference, not deliverable)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782076220664655001,"uuid":"9f5aa53c-02f5-432d-a5af-3aa7f30a9dbc"}